docs.lead_paragraph: China features prominently in the rhetoric of presumed Republican presidential candidate Donald Trump, who accuses the country of stealing American jobs and cheating at global trade. In China itself, though, he's only now emerging as a public figure, despite fame elsewhere for his voluble utterances, high-profile businesses and reality TV show.

headline.main: As in US, Trump Draws Strong Reactions in China
headline.print_headline: As in US, Trump Draws Strong Reactions in China

docs.snippet: Embracing a version of American identity that is not based on ethnicity....
docs.lead_paragraph: Embracing a version of American identity that is not based on ethnicity.
docs.abstract: Op-Ed article by public policy professor Roberto Suro underscores how different young Latinos are politically from Latino establishment, fact most evident in their ardent support for Sen Bernie Sanders over Hillary Clinton; observes young Latinos are pushing forward with politics defined by universal values, as opposed to those defined by ethnicity or heritage.

headline.main: The Real ‘Trump Effect’ for Young Latinos
headline.print_headline: The All-American Values of Young Latinos
